OL,6,FIn November, Richardson was found
OL,7,Fguilty of preparing for acts of
OL,8,Fterrorism, two counts of collecting
OL,9,Finformation likely to be useful to a
OL,10,Fperson committing or preparing an act
OL,11,Fof terrorism, and three counts of
OL,12,Fdistributing terrorist publications.
OL,14,FRichardson, of Oliver Close, Howden,
OL,15,Fwas handed a discretionary life
OL,16,Fsentence and told he must serve a
OL,17,Fminimum term of 16 years.
